into account both cultural contexts and the author's non-fictional writings, the book's main focus is on configurations of gender and sexuality. Bowen's fiction constitutes an exploration of the unstable and destabilizing effects of sexuality in the interdependent processes of subjectivity and what she herself referred to as so-called reality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aFeminism and literaturexHistoryx20th centuryxIreland. 0aFeminism and literaturezIrelandxHistoryy20th century. 0aLesbiansxIntellectual lifexIreland. 0aLesbianszIrelandxIntellectual life. 0aLesbians' writings, EnglishxHistory and criticismxIreland. 0aLesbians' writings, EnglishzIrelandxHistory and criticism. 0aWomen and literaturexHistoryx20th centuryxIreland. 0aWomen and literaturezIrelandxHistoryy20th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / LGBT.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814744888423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814744888.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK